                <note rend="inline" type="source">821.6363/390: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Colombia</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Piles</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Bogotá</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1928-05-15T11:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">May 15, 1928—11 a.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/>[Received 3:15 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>29. Press reports Minister of Industry has sent circular telegram to Governors
                    and Intendants, categorically instructing them to carry out provisions of
                    Petroleum Decree Number 150 with respect to drilling without Government permit.
                    Same telegram stated to call the attention of notaries and magistrates to their
                    duties under decree, such as forwarding to the Minister of Industry copies of
                    all contracts celebrated in the last 10 years and in future (see article 15),
                    adding that Minister is prepared to impose penalties for infractions stipulated
                    in decree. Matter will have my careful attention.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Piles</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
